article.description: — Johni Broome had 22 points and 13 rebounds as Morehead State won its ninth straight game, beating Tennessee Tech 74-55 on Saturday.
article.headline: Broome leads Morehead St. over Tennessee Tech 74-55
article.linkText: Broome leads Morehead St. over Tennessee Tech 74-55
article.story: COOKEVILLE, Tenn. -- — Johni Broome had 22 points and 13 rebounds as Morehead State won its ninth straight game, beating Tennessee Tech 74-55 on Saturday. Skyelar Potter had 15 points for Morehead State (13-6, 10-2 Ohio Valley Conference). James Baker, Jr. added 10 points. Jr. Clay had 17 points for the Golden Eagles (2-16, 2-9). Shandon Goldman added 11 points and eight rebounds. Keishawn Davidson had six assists. Tennessee Tech scored 23 points in the second half, a season low for the team. Morehead State defeated Tennessee Tech 57-54 on Jan. 7. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
